s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2283:"<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512.png" rel="lightbox-0"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-100x100.png" alt="logo-512x512" width="100" height="100" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-699" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-100x100.png 100w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-300x300.png 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-150x150.png 150w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-200x200.png 200w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-450x450.png 450w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-90x90.png 90w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512.png 512w" sizes="(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px" /></a>A small update with a few tweaks to the overall dashboard. AdRotate 3.14.1 is tested to work on WordPress 4.4 with no known issues. An obsolete field in the database has been removed, old adverts will be migrated over to the &#8220;new&#8221; system which was introduce almost 2 years ago.</p>\n<h2>changes</h2>\n<div class="shortcode-unorderedlist arrow">\n<ul>\n<li>[change] Few dashboard updates, better wording and such</li>\n<li>[change] Removed obsolete &#8216;link&#8217; column from database</li>\n<li>[i18n] Updated translation strings</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2>Phoney hamburgers</h2>\n<p>When you order a hamburger you expect a round pattie. Some lettuce, tomato and a circular piece of ground beef.</p>\n<p>Not this &#8211;<br />\n<a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/filipino-hamburger.jpg" rel="lightbox-1"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/filipino-hamburger-1024x768.jpg" alt="filipino-hamburger" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-9626" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/filipino-hamburger-300x225.jpg 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/filipino-hamburger-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/filipino-hamburger.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></p>\n<p>Even though the taste was ok, it&#8217;s not a hamburger.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:38:"Automatic update bug – Fixed, but…";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"https://ajdg.solutions/2015/12/05/automatic-update-bug-fixed-but/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 04 Dec 2015 19:08:04 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"Plugins";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"bugfix";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"woocommerce";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"adrotate";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"annoying";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"api";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"https://ajdg.solutions/?p=9628";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:349:"While updating the slug for AdRotate Pro I&#8217;ve discovered a bug in the automatic updating system for AdRotate Pro and Merchant E-solutions for WooCommerce. While building the system I never accounted for plugin slugs that have a dash in them. So I happily used dashes elsewhere. This breaks the downloads of updates. Yay! AdRotate Pro [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Arnan";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3125:"<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/ajdg-logo-compact.png" rel="lightbox-0"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/ajdg-logo-compact.png" alt="ajdg-logo-compact" width="125" height="125" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-8975" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/ajdg-logo-compact-100x100.png 100w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/ajdg-logo-compact.png 125w" sizes="(max-width: 125px) 100vw, 125px" /></a>While updating the slug for AdRotate Pro I&#8217;ve discovered a bug in the automatic updating system for AdRotate Pro and Merchant E-solutions for WooCommerce. While building the system I never accounted for plugin slugs that have a dash in them. So I happily used dashes elsewhere. This breaks the downloads of updates. Yay! <img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-includes/images/smilies/frownie.png" alt=":(" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p>\n<h2>AdRotate Pro</h2>\n<p>WordPress may not see the update for AdRotate Pro 3.18.2. In my tests I would get the update for AdRotate Free or no update at all. On 2 of the 3 sites I tested this on I got no update notification at all.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re missing the update notification or get an update for AdRotate Free instead you should update manually. Accidentally installing AdRotate Free will not break your adverts but will disable the AdRotate Pro features (including having multiple schedules for adverts).</p>\n<p>You can do a manual update quickly and easily following this guide &#8211; <a href="https://ajdg.solutions/manuals/adrotate-manuals/upgrade-adrotate-pro-to-a-newer-version/">Upgrade AdRotate Pro to a newer version</a>.</p>\n<h2>Merchant E-Solutions</h2>\n<p>For Merchant E-Solutions things are a bit more straightforward. The plugin already has the right slugs. Now that the update server can understand the &#8216;merchant-esolutions&#8217; slug updates will be offered as advertised.</p>\n<h2>When running into trouble</h2>\n<p>If you&#8217;re having trouble with updating to AdRotate Pro version 3.18.2 or Merchant E-Solutions version 1.0.1. Let me know as soon as possible via the <a href="https://ajdg.solutions/contact/">contact form</a>. </p>\n<p>Include any errors or notifications you saw while updating. Also create/share an admin account for your WordPress dashboard and a (s)FTP login so I can go in and fix things quickly. Sending complete and accurate information will get this sorted faster.</p>\n<h2>Golden skies!</h2>\n<p>If you&#8217;re on a boat at the right time, you may see this.<br />\n<a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/sunset.jpg" rel="lightbox-1"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/sunset-1024x768.jpg" alt="sunset" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-9633" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/sunset-300x225.jpg 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/sunset-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/sunset.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:48:"AdRotate Pro 3.18.2 – WordPress 4.4 compatible";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:79:"https://ajdg.solutions/2015/12/05/adrotate-pro-3-18-2-wordpress-4-4-compatible/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 04 Dec 2015 17:18:44 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"AdRotate Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"adrotate";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"compatible";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"pro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"geotargeting";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"https://ajdg.solutions/?p=9622";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:315:"A small update with a few tweaks and a minor fix for Geo Targeting. A few people using old settings were affected. AdRotate Pro 3.18.2 is tested to work on WordPress 4.4 with no known issues. changes I&#8217;ve met the Mayor! I&#8217;m not much of a christmas guy. But the lights are fascinating. Over the [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Arnan";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2475:"<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512.png" rel="lightbox-0"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-100x100.png" alt="logo-512x512" width="100" height="100" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-699" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-100x100.png 100w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-300x300.png 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-150x150.png 150w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-200x200.png 200w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-450x450.png 450w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-90x90.png 90w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512.png 512w" sizes="(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px" /></a>A small update with a few tweaks and a minor fix for Geo Targeting. A few people using old settings were affected. AdRotate Pro 3.18.2 is tested to work on WordPress 4.4 with no known issues.</p>\n<h2>changes</h2>\n<div class="shortcode-unorderedlist arrow">\n<ul>\n<li>[change] Tweaks to Geo Targeting settings</li>\n<li>[change] Dashboard tweaks</li>\n<li>[fix] Telize/GeoBytes not redirecting to AdRotate Geo properly</li>\n<li>[i18n] Updated translation strings</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2>I&#8217;ve met the Mayor!</h2>\n<p>I&#8217;m not much of a christmas guy. But the lights are fascinating. Over the past days they&#8217;ve prettied up the Municipal Hall in Puerto Galera. I met Mayor Hubbert Dolor as he was walking to his car. A nice guy and very approachable, we shook hands <img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p>\n<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/municipal-hall-puerto-galera.jpg" rel="lightbox-1"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/municipal-hall-puerto-galera-1024x768.jpg" alt="municipal-hall-puerto-galera" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-9623" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/municipal-hall-puerto-galera-300x225.jpg 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/municipal-hall-puerto-galera-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/municipal-hall-puerto-galera.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"AdRotate Pro 3.18.1 – Geo updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:66:"https://ajdg.solutions/2015/12/02/adrotate-pro-3-18-1-geo-updates/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 01 Dec 2015 17:22:17 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"AdRotate Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"adrotate";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"pro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"api";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"geotargeting";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"https://ajdg.solutions/?p=9440";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:357:"A small update mainly aimed at Geo Targeting and some maintenance. The settings dashboards have had some tweaks so options are better explained. Some on/off settings were ambiguous. While updating that I came across a slew of strings that were in the translation files, but weren&#8217;t actually translated. This has been fixed too. Geo Targeting [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Arnan";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4060:"<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512.png" rel="lightbox-0"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-100x100.png" alt="logo-512x512" width="100" height="100" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-699" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-100x100.png 100w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-300x300.png 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-150x150.png 150w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-200x200.png 200w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-450x450.png 450w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-90x90.png 90w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512.png 512w" sizes="(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px" /></a>A small update mainly aimed at Geo Targeting and some maintenance. The settings dashboards have had some tweaks so options are better explained. Some on/off settings were ambiguous. While updating that I came across a slew of strings that were in the translation files, but weren&#8217;t actually translated. This has been fixed too.</p>\n<h2>Geo Targeting</h2>\n<p>With the closing of Telize as a public Geo Lookup service AdRotate will no longer support Telize. Their offering of free data for money is not something I wish to support. AdRotate Geo uses the same database and is free to use to AdRotate Pro users.</p>\n<p>If you currently have Telize selected it will silently fail and redirect to AdRotate Geo starting with AdRotate 3.18.1. Also starting with this version of AdRotate Pro you&#8217;ll get 75000 free lookups per day, up from 50000. The AdRotate Geo API has been updated to version, which versions 3.18.1 and up will utilise. This API should be a tiny bit faster, too. Win win!</p>\n<p>Another nice update is that ipv6 now actually works for both MaxMind and AdRotate Geo. It sort-off kinda worked already. But using the updated AdRotate Geo API the ipv6 IP&#8217;s will actually validate and work as-is. AdRotate Geo API 1 would accept, but not validate the IP.<br />\nMaxMind already quietly supported ipv6 IP&#8217;s.</p>\n<h2>Name change</h2>\n<p>After updating AdRotate Pro, the plugin may not re-activate for some people.<br />\nThis is related to the main file name changing name. WordPress is standardising their stuff and requires all plugin names and such to be up to date.<br />\nAdRotate Pro still used the slug for the free version &#8211; Which works fine. But this is no longer allowed.</p>\n<p>In my tests on a development site and live site the plugin update went fine. No re-activation required. But for you this may be different. Just activate the plugin manually and things will work again.</p>\n<h2>Changelog</h2>\n<div class="shortcode-unorderedlist arrow">\n<ul>\n<li>[new] ipv6 support for AdRotate Geo</li>\n<li>[update] AdRotate Geo now allows 75k lookups per day</li>\n<li>[update] ipv6 support for MaxMind</li>\n<li>[change] Telize no longer supported</li>\n<li>[change] Few dashboard updates, better wording and such</li>\n<li>[change] Removed obsolete &#8216;link&#8217; column from adrotate table</li>\n<li>[fix] i18n text domain for some strings</li>\n<li>[i18n] Translation files updated</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2>How many houses</h2>\n<p>I passed by these slums while walking towards the harbour this afternoon.<br />\nGuess how many houses are in this picture?</p>\n<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/batangas-slums.jpg" rel="lightbox-1"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/batangas-slums-1024x768.jpg" alt="batangas-slums" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-9442" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/batangas-slums-300x225.jpg 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/batangas-slums-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/batangas-slums.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:38:"AdRotate Pro: Geo Targeting and Telize";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:72:"https://ajdg.solutions/2015/11/26/adrotate-pro-geo-targeting-and-telize/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 25 Nov 2015 20:07:01 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"AdRotate Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"adrotate";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"services";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"pro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"api";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"geotargeting";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"https://ajdg.solutions/?p=9234";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:331:"Just a quick service announcement for AdRotate Pro users using Geo Targeting. Telize more-or-less shut down as of November 15th 2015. They cite abuse and overuse of their servers as a reason. From what I gather a Geo Api will still be offered as a paid &#8216;solution&#8217;. However, since they use a free database just [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Arnan";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2652:"<p>Just a quick service announcement for AdRotate Pro users using Geo Targeting. Telize more-or-less shut down as of November 15th 2015. They cite abuse and overuse of their servers as a reason. From what I gather a Geo Api will still be offered as a paid &#8216;solution&#8217;. However, since they use a free database just like AdRotate Geo does I do not believe Telize is a viable option any longer.</p>\n<p>AdRotate Pro v3.18.1 (or v3.19) will remove support for Telize, leaving MaxMind and AdRotate Geo as the alternatives. If you&#8217;re using Telize now, please change your setting to AdRotate Geo or buy a subscription from Maxmind &#8211; Links for that are in AdRotate Settings.</p>\n<p>MaxMind is a paid service. Using their highly accurate and fast GeoIP2 Precision Services &#8211; This is well worth the money if you&#8217;re serious about Geo Targeting. They offer a service for cities or, somewhat cheaper, for countries. </p>\n<p>AdRotate Geo continues to offer the free GeoLITE2 database. I&#8217;m currently working on a optimised version of my API software. Using AdRotate Geo requires a valid AdRotate Pro license. A FREE subscription for AdRotate Geo registers automatically when you select AdRotate Geo.</p>\n<p>Continued attempts to use Telize after you install AdRotate Pro 3.18.1 (or 3.19) will be redirected to AdRotate Geo to ensure that Geo Targeting works. But please check and update your settings if required, too. Better safe than sorry!</p>\n<h2>The flow of things</h2>\n<p>Earlier today I dug a small trench to get a small river to flow again into the sea. High tide had changed the sand on the beach blocking the stream. As a result a huge reservoir was building up. Normally there would be a small stream crossing the beach. </p>\n<p>After nurturing the trench for a few minutes water started to flow freely and a little while later things got a bit out of hand and the reservoir overflowed my narrow trench. Just over an hour later it had turned into this strong current you see in the photo.</p>\n<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/arnan-crossing-stream.jpg" rel="lightbox-0"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/arnan-crossing-stream-768x1024.jpg" alt="arnan-crossing-stream" width="768" height="1024" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-9235" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/arnan-crossing-stream-225x300.jpg 225w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/arnan-crossing-stream-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/arnan-crossing-stream.jpg 960w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" /></a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:37:"AdRotate Free 3.14 – Available now!";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"https://ajdg.solutions/2015/11/24/adrotate-free-3-14-available-now/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 11:50:43 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"AdRotate Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"bugfix";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"improvements";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"adrotate";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"free";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"https://ajdg.solutions/?p=9052";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:341:"A bunch of tweaks and improvements including sortable columns in the dashboard. The dynamic mode can now be turned off for mobile devices. In recent versions it was disabled without an option. This is of-course to maintain a working advert on smaller devices if you don&#8217;t use mobile adverts. Not every theme handles the fixed [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Arnan";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2533:"<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512.png" rel="lightbox-0"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-100x100.png" alt="logo-512x512" width="100" height="100" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-699" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-100x100.png 100w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-300x300.png 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-150x150.png 150w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-200x200.png 200w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-450x450.png 450w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512-90x90.png 90w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/logo-512x512.png 512w" sizes="(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px" /></a>A bunch of tweaks and improvements including sortable columns in the dashboard. The dynamic mode can now be turned off for mobile devices. In recent versions it was disabled without an option. This is of-course to maintain a working advert on smaller devices if you don&#8217;t use mobile adverts. Not every theme handles the fixed size very well. Depending on your theme this option then makes sense or not. Also the exporting of adverts didn&#8217;t always work. This has been fixed.</p>\n<h2>Changes</h2>\n<div class="shortcode-unorderedlist arrow">\n<ul>\n<li>[new] Option to disable dynamic mode on mobile devices</li>\n<li>[new] Basic sortable columns for most dashboard tables</li>\n<li>[fix] Exporting adverts not always working for some users</li>\n<li>[change] Responsive feature is now deprecated</li>\n<li>[i18n] Updated translation files</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2>When not doing internet things</h2>\n<p>A little while ago I stumbled on a bunch of fishermen who were a few hands short reeling in their net. So I helped them pull the thing onto the beach. It was loaded with fish.</p>\n<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/arnan-fishing.jpg" rel="lightbox-1"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/arnan-fishing-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-9056" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/arnan-fishing-300x225.jpg 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/arnan-fishing-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/arnan-fishing.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:43:"Omnikassa for WooCommerce 1.3.3 – Updated";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"https://ajdg.solutions/2015/11/24/omnikassa-for-woocommerce-1-3-3-updated/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 04:05:23 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:23:"Payment Gateway Plugins";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"woocommerce";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"improvements";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"fix";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"omnikassa";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"https://ajdg.solutions/?p=9066";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:365:"A small maintenance update fixing the dashboard links in the plugin to more relevant items. Also the Dutch translation has been updated. Some typos removed. Changes Automatic updates OmniKassa (OmniCard) for WooCommerce has automatic updates. This was introduced earlier this year in version 1.3.2. If you have this version already the update will show in [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Arnan";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2276:"<p><a href="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/wc-omnicard-logo.jpg" rel="lightbox-0"><img src="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/wc-omnicard-logo-100x100.jpg" alt="wc-omnicard-logo" width="100" height="100" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-1021" srcset="https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/wc-omnicard-logo-100x100.jpg 100w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/wc-omnicard-logo-300x300.jpg 300w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/wc-omnicard-logo-150x150.jpg 150w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/wc-omnicard-logo-260x260.jpg 260w, https://ajdg.solutions/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/wc-omnicard-logo.jpg 380w" sizes="(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px" /></a>A small maintenance update fixing the dashboard links in the plugin to more relevant items. Also the Dutch translation has been updated. Some typos removed.</p>\n<h2>Changes</h2>\n<div class="shortcode-unorderedlist arrow">\n<ul>\n<li>[change] Updated credits links</li>\n<li>[i18n] Updated Dutch translation</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2>Automatic updates</h2>\n<p>OmniKassa (OmniCard) for WooCommerce has automatic updates. This was introduced earlier this year in version 1.3.2. If you have this version already the update will show in your websites dashboard. With a valid license you can update the plugin automatically just like other plugins.</p>\n<h3>Manual update steps:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Download the latest version from your <a href="https://ajdg.solutions/my-account/">account</a> on this website.</li>\n<li>Unzip the ‘omnicard.zip’ file.</li>\n<li>Log in to your website files with your favorite (s)FTP account.</li>\n<li>Browse to the ‘/wp-content/plugins/’ folder.</li>\n<li>Upload the unzipped ‘omnicard’ folder to the ‘wp-content/plugins/’ folder and overwrite the current folder.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Because this update is rather small/minor, you do not have to disable the plugin while updating. For other updates disabling the plugin before updating is advised.</em></p>\n<p>If you need help updating the plugin I can install the update for a small fee.<br />\nPlease select the Installation service from the <a href="https://ajdg.solutions/products/omnikassa-for-woocommerce/">Omnikassa product page</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:61